\sqrt{1+x} =(1+x)^{1/2} = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \binom{1/2}{k}x^k 
\binom{1/2}{1} = \frac12
\binom{1/2}{2} = \frac12\left(\frac{-1/2}{2}\right) = \frac{-1}{8}
\binom{1/2}{3} = -\frac18\left(\frac{-3/2}{3}\right) = \frac{1}{16}
\sqrt{1+x} =1+\frac{x}{2}-\frac{x^2}{8}+\frac{x^3}{16} \pm ... 
